11.body: Misinformation: The digital landscape is rife with misleading or false information, making it increasingly difficult for individuals to discern truth from fiction. Misrepresentation: Disparate viewpoints are frequently distorted or misrepresented, hindering genuine understanding and dialogue. Echo Chambers: Individuals tend to engage primarily with like-minded individuals, reinforcing existing beliefs and discouraging meaningful discourse with those holding differing perspectives. Missed Opportunities: The absence of a platform that facilitates fluid, constructive interactions limits the potential for growth, learning, and progress.
11.breadcrumbs: Vivada » Converging Challenges » Misinformation, Misrepresentation, and Echo Chambers
11.title: Misinformation, Misrepresentation, and Echo Chambers

12.body: Our platform aims to revolutionize discourse by providing a structured framework for users to present their viewpoints. While the content remains user-generated, we standardize the format, allowing for more focused and transparent discussions.
12.title: Solution Overview

13.body: Specific Claim Format: Users articulate their opinions using a predefined format, ensuring clarity and coherence in their arguments. Neutral Content Channeling: We channel posts based on format, not content, preserving individual expression while enhancing readability and understanding. Transparency in Discourse: By bringing implicit thoughts into the open, our platform fosters open and transparent conversations. Face-to-Face Engagement: Instead of monologues, users engage directly, fostering dynamic interactions and enabling the best argument to prevail. Counter-Evidence Research: Users are encouraged to research counter-evidence for claims they disagree with, promoting critical thinking and challenging entrenched beliefs.
13.title: Key Features

14.body: User Registration: Users create profiles, providing basic information and preferences. Claim Creation: Users submit claims using the specified format, prompting structured discussions. Aggregated Spaces: Claims from diverse perspectives are aggregated, ensuring a rich and varied discussion environment. Research Resources: Users have access to a wealth of resources for fact-checking and counter-argument development. Engagement Metrics: Track and evaluate discussions based on factors such as engagement levels, quality of arguments, and information validity.
14.breadcrumbs: Vivada » Converging Challenges » » How It Works
14.title: How It Works

15.body: Fact-Driven Discourse: Encourages evidence-based discussions, reducing the spread of misinformation. Enhanced Understanding: Promotes clear articulation of viewpoints, reducing misrepresentation. Diverse Engagement: Facilitates interactions between individuals with varied perspectives, breaking down echo chambers. Intellectual Growth: Encourages critical thinking and research, leading to a more informed and open-minded community.
15.title: Benefits

16.body: The platform will be developed using modern web technologies, ensuring accessibility and user-friendliness. It will incorporate robust data handling practices to protect user privacy and security.
16.title: Implementation

17.body: AI-Driven Moderation: Implementing AI algorithms to assist in content moderation, ensuring a safe and respectful environment. Multi-Lingual Support: Expanding the platform to accommodate users from different linguistic backgrounds. Integration with Social Media Platforms: Allowing users to share content seamlessly across various social media channels.
17.title: Future Developments

18.body: Our platform seeks to bridge the gaps in online discourse by providing a structured, transparent, and engaging environment for individuals to exchange ideas. By standardizing format and encouraging research, we aim to foster a community where the best arguments prevail, ultimately driving intellectual growth and progress.
18.title: Conclusion

23.body: Users have the ability to contribute multiple definitions to specific terms or phrases. For example, a term like "Dharma" can have various interpretations (e.g., Dharma 1, Dharma 1.2, or Dharma 3). When using a term, users are prompted to select the appropriate definition from the available options.
23.breadcrumbs: Vivada » User Workflow » 3. Adding Definitions to Specific Terms
23.title: 3. Adding Definitions to Specific Terms

24.body: Users can engage with others' claims using a set of standardized responses, fostering a structured and focused exchange of ideas. These responses include: Agree : Expressing alignment with a given claim. Disagree : Offering a counter-perspective or providing evidence against a claim. Seek Clarification : Requesting further information or context on a claim. Add Evidence : Supplementing a claim with additional supporting information. Challenge Definitions : Questioning or suggesting alterations to the definitions provided for specific terms.

31.body: Claims/Incidents Topics/Timelines Circles People/Organizations Links List of entities that are part of the application:- Claim - Any unsubstantiated claim opinions, speculations etc with an optional justification text Incident - Any physical event with location and datetime data about it along with context and evidence. Citation - Any statement that is extracted from a publication(book, video, podcast,News paper article, blog, online comment..etc) and assigned to a public profile of a person on the platform. Topic - Could be a question or a debate topic or a specific phenomenon Profile - Any user can create a public profile for any individual or organization in order to cite them. Link - A relationship established between two entities. Each entity pairing can have multiple types of relationships, which is defined by the type of connector used in the link. User-Claim Link Claim-Claim Link Claim-Topic Link Claim-Circle Link User-Topic Link User-Circle Link Circle-Circle Link Connector - An identifier for the different types of relationships that can exist between two entities. For eg. Claim A ←-[ Supports]--> Claim B. Here [Supports] is a connector. A connector is used to define the nature of the link between two entities. Timeline - What a topic is, but with only incidents. Each incident has a timestamp and each timeline has a starting and ending time and a description to signifiy what this timeline is tracking Circle - Collection of claims/topics/incidents/timelines/sub-circles based on location, category or organization. Location-based circles Interest-based circles Organizational circles (Private communities) Argument - Collection of claims/citations/incidents that are linked to each other with connectors. More info - Vivada.io UX - Google Sheets
31.title: Entities:-

32.body: Entity-related features :- Browse and follow feeds for each entity type Interact with entities with entity-specific action (for eg. agree/disagree for claims) Create/delete the entities Argument map - A global argument map which will visually render the entities and the network of relationships that they have in the network of user-generated content. This argument can be fine-tuned to show only the content of interest using filters for circle, user, claim etc. Store - Redeem points and badges for items available on the store (It would be similar to a credit card reward points redemption experience). __Communities __- Premium users can create their own private community and set up custom features like verification, paywall, customized privacy hierarchy within the communities. Settings Notification preferences Privacy settings Profile settings Account settings Legal Privacy Policy Terms & Conditions Moderation Policy

5.body: " Vivada " is a groundbreaking platform designed to address the challenges of misinformation, misrepresentation, and echo chambers in today's digital landscape. It provides a structured framework for users to present their viewpoints, promoting transparent and constructive conversations. By standardizing claim formats and encouraging evidence-based discussions, the platform aims to foster a community where the best arguments prevail, leading to intellectual growth and progress. Through user-friendly implementation and future developments like AI-driven moderation and multi-lingual support, __Vivada __aspires to revolutionize online discourse for a diverse and informed community. Vivada is a platform designed to facilitate constructive discourse by allowing users to post claims, provide supporting bases for those claims, and contribute multiple definitions to specific terms. This feature enriches discussions by ensuring that users select the appropriate definition when using particular terms. The platform also encourages interaction with others' claims through a set of standardized responses.
5.title: Overview

73.body: Please follow these steps to get your email account setup on both your phone and your computer so that you don’t miss anything. Prerequisites: Email from HR with your credentials Phone and computer with internet connection Steps: Get your email and password from the email that you’ve received from HR Download Microsoft Outlook on your phone and computer. Click here to access the official download Open outlook and click on Add account and enter your email ID (from the email from the HR) into Outlook. Enter the following details to complete your account setup Username - Password - Incoming server - mail.vivada.tech (Port 993) Outgoing server - mail.vivada.tech (Port 465) Use SSL to connect - True With these simple steps you should be able to access your emails on your device. Please make sure to complete the process for both your computer and mobile phone so that you’re in sync. If you have any further questions, please watch this video or reach out to hr@vivada.tech The next step is to connect to the VPN, where you may also change your password. Please follow the steps here to connect to VPN.

79.body: VS Code . Please install the following VS Code extensions. Common GitLens — Git supercharged Prettier - Code formatter Frontend extensions Angular Language Service Backend extensions Docker Python Django Set default terminal on VS Code NVM __ __- This is the node version manager that allows you to have multiple versions of node on your machine. Please install it as per the instructions and ensure that you create a .bashrc file with the following content in the root folder. Follow these steps:- Open VS Code and open a Git bash terminal Enter cd Enter code .bashrc Add the following code in the empty .bashrc file export NVM_DIR="$([ -z "${XDG_CONFIG_HOME-}" ] && printf %s "${HOME}/.nvm" || printf %s "${XDG_CONFIG_HOME}/nvm")" [ -s "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" ] && \. "$NVM_DIR/nvm.sh" This loads nvm. This will ensure that npm loads every time you open the terminal.
